    "body": "> Im using a PoA private network with a blocktime of 0. I can broadcast transactions and they are mined as they should.\r\nIf I send a transaction with gasPrice too low, all the miners ignore this transaction.\r\n\r\nYou can configure minimum gas price for mining a transaction with `--miner.gasprice value` (default value is 1 gwei = 1,000,000,000 wei, see [docs](https://geth.ethereum.org/docs/interface/command-line-options)).\r\n\r\n> That's OK for me but then all future transactions from this account get ignored by miners even if they have the correct gasPrice.\r\n\r\nI guess that If large amount of transactions are submitted from a sender, miner assume that the sender perform DDoS attack, and ignore all transactions from the sender. To solve this problem, increase the price of gas and re-submit the transactions.\r\n\r\n",
